fr:resource.fr:resource-source:
\begin {prooftree}
\hypo {p \land  q, r \lor  s \;/\; p \land  s}
\infer 1[]{\top  \land  (p \land  q), (t \rightarrow  s) \lor  s \;/\; \top  \land  s}
\end {prooftree}

fr:mainmatter.html:p:
It is not.
Here's a counterexample: a Boolean valuation v where:

v(p) = \mathsf {\mathbf {T}}

v(q) = \mathsf {\mathbf {T}}

v(s) = \mathsf {\mathbf {F}}

v(t) = \mathsf {\mathbf {F}}
